transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Good morning, mister Smith. I'm doctor Patel. What brings you in today?

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Morning, doctor. I have been feeling really tired lately.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: And I have this persistent cough that won't go away.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: It's been going on for about three weeks now.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: I see.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: The cough dry, or are you bringing up any mucus?

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: It's almost dry.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: But sometimes I do cough up some yellowish mucus.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Have you noticed any fever, chills, or night sweats?

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Yes. I've had mild fevers on and off.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: And I wake up sweating at night.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Any shortness of breath or chest pain

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: I do feel a little short of breath when we

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: were walking up the stairs, but I haven't had any real chest pain.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Have you had any unintended pain?

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Yes. I have lost about seven pounds in the last month.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: But I haven't changed my diet.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Do you smoke or have a history of smoking?

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: I used to smoke about a pack a day for fifteen years.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: But I quit five years ago.

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: Have you traveled recently or been around anyone who is sick?

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: No recent travel, but I work in a

transcript.speaker: Speaker
transcript.text: homeless shelter, so I am around a lot of different people.

transcript.text: Got it. Like, you run some tests during a chest x-ray and simpler work.
